# Project Structure Guide

This project is a web-based simulation of the Windows XP desktop environment, used as a creative portfolio.

## Main Entry Point
- [index.html](mdc:index.html): Loads the desktop simulation and all core scripts/styles.

## Source Code
- [src/scripts/](mdc:src/scripts): Core logic, utilities, and GUI managers.
  - [main.js](mdc:src/scripts/main.js): Main script for initializing the environment.
  - [utils/](mdc:src/scripts/utils): Utility modules (menu bar, toolbar, event bus, etc.).
  - [gui/](mdc:src/scripts/gui): GUI managers (window, desktop, taskbar, start menu).
- [src/apps/](mdc:src/apps): Individual app modules (About Me, Notepad, etc.), each in its own subdirectory.

## Styles
- [src/styles/](mdc:src/styles): Main, GUI, and utility CSS files.
  - [gui/](mdc:src/styles/gui): Styles for desktop, windows, taskbar, start menu, etc.
  - [utils/](mdc:src/styles/utils): Utility and reset styles.

## Assets
- [assets/](mdc:assets): Images, icons, sounds, and GUI assets.
  - [gui/](mdc:assets/gui): GUI-related images and icons.

## Documentation
- [docs/README.md](mdc:docs/README.md): Project overview and documentation index.
- [docs/ISSUES.md](mdc:docs/ISSUES.md): Implementation notes, UI conventions, and known issues.

